{
  "video_id": "Rcm3rPz_Q94",
  "title": "The real reason why mosquitoes buzz | DIY Neuroscience, a TED series",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Krystian Aparta"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12100.0,
      "end_time": 14604.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 14628.0,
      "end_time": 17494.0,
      "text": "Greg Gage: We&#39;ve all heard the annoying sound of a mosquito,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17518.0,
      "end_time": 19740.0,
      "text": "and we will stop at nothing to make it go away."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 19764.0,
      "end_time": 21669.0,
      "text": "While this sound may be maddening to us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21693.0,
      "end_time": 23612.0,
      "text": "perhaps it&#39;s music to a mosquito&#39;s ears."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23636.0,
      "end_time": 27869.0,
      "text": "The mosquito&#39;s nervous system has almost as many sensory auditory cells as we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 28370.0,
      "end_time": 30910.0,
      "text": "But why would they have so many in such a small body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 30934.0,
      "end_time": 33481.0,
      "text": "and why would they need to be so sensitive to sounds?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 33505.0,
      "end_time": 34698.0,
      "text": "The answer is love."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 34722.0,
      "end_time": 36635.0,
      "text": "[DIY Neuroscience]"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 36665.0,
      "end_time": 39605.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39635.0,
      "end_time": 41730.0,
      "text": "As humans, we do a lot to attract each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41755.0,
      "end_time": 43150.0,
      "text": "Some things are conscious --"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43174.0,
      "end_time": 45274.0,
      "text": "we put on makeup and make sure we smell nice."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45298.0,
      "end_time": 46524.0,
      "text": "And some are unconscious."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 46548.0,
      "end_time": 50168.0,
      "text": "You may unconsciously point your body or even sit closer to someone you like."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 50192.0,
      "end_time": 53579.0,
      "text": "These are courtship behaviors, and a lot of animals have them."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 53603.0,
      "end_time": 55205.0,
      "text": "And mosquitoes are no different."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 55229.0,
      "end_time": 58522.0,
      "text": "So Haley&#39;s been spending her summer bravely listening to mosquitoes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 58547.0,
      "end_time": 60468.0,
      "text": "and what she observed may surprise you."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 60492.0,
      "end_time": 63922.0,
      "text": "So we want to investigate how the mosquitoes make their song."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 63947.0,
      "end_time": 66486.0,
      "text": "So Haley, how do we record their wing beats?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 66510.0,
      "end_time": 68295.0,
      "text": "Haley Smith: We need to tether them."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 68319.0,
      "end_time": 73980.0,
      "text": "First, we anesthetize them in a fridge or a bed of ice."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 73122.0,
      "end_time": 76575.0,
      "text": "And then I transfer them to this petri dish of ice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 76599.0,
      "end_time": 78505.0,
      "text": "just to get them even more anesthetized."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 78529.0,
      "end_time": 82530.0,
      "text": "Next, I take an insect pin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 82770.0,
      "end_time": 86554.0,
      "text": "and what I do is put a tiny little dab of superglue on this pin."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 86578.0,
      "end_time": 90318.0,
      "text": "I want to make sure that I get it on his thorax above his wings"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90342.0,
      "end_time": 93795.0,
      "text": "so that when he is suspended, his wings are still free to move."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93819.0,
      "end_time": 94978.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s one down."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95200.0,
      "end_time": 97527.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really hard to catch male mosquitoes in the wild"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97551.0,
      "end_time": 101804.0,
      "text": "because females are the only mosquitoes that are attracted to humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101828.0,
      "end_time": 103424.0,
      "text": "They feed on human blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103448.0,
      "end_time": 108768.0,
      "text": "And now, we can try to get some recordings from them."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 108793.0,
      "end_time": 111900.0,
      "text": "So this is the stand that I use to hold them."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 111114.0,
      "end_time": 113269.0,
      "text": "I like to place it right over the microphone"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 113293.0,
      "end_time": 116840.0,
      "text": "so that I can get a recording of the buzzing that you hear."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 116108.0,
      "end_time": 119109.0,
      "text": "That sound is generated by how fast they&#39;re beating their wings."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 119133.0,
      "end_time": 120371.0,
      "text": "This is a male."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 120395.0,
      "end_time": 124710.0,
      "text": "The males have very bushy antennae, and they look kind of feathery."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 124950.0,
      "end_time": 126611.0,
      "text": "And they are also much smaller."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 126635.0,
      "end_time": 129899.0,
      "text": "GG: So he&#39;s flying at around 600 hertz."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 129923.0,
      "end_time": 132400.0,
      "text": "Can we try a female mosquito?"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 132424.0,
      "end_time": 134454.0,
      "text": "HS: Sure, here we go."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 134478.0,
      "end_time": 140129.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing, lower pitch)"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 140153.0,
      "end_time": 141399.0,
      "text": "GG: Wow."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 141423.0,
      "end_time": 143959.0,
      "text": "HS: This is a much lower frequency than the male."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 143983.0,
      "end_time": 146118.0,
      "text": "GG: Yeah, it sounds completely different."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 146142.0,
      "end_time": 147999.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 148230.0,
      "end_time": 150499.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing, lower pitch)"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 150523.0,
      "end_time": 152887.0,
      "text": "So is it because they&#39;re two different mosquitoes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 152911.0,
      "end_time": 154592.0,
      "text": "or because they&#39;re male and female?"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 154616.0,
      "end_time": 156533.0,
      "text": "HS: It&#39;s because they&#39;re male and female."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 156557.0,
      "end_time": 158197.0,
      "text": "GG: Alright, let&#39;s verify that."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 158222.0,
      "end_time": 160809.0,
      "text": "Can you bring in another female and see if she sounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 160833.0,
      "end_time": 162707.0,
      "text": "like mosquito A or mosquito B?"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 162731.0,
      "end_time": 163882.0,
      "text": "HS: Yeah."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 163906.0,
      "end_time": 165659.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing, lower pitch)"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 165683.0,
      "end_time": 167755.0,
      "text": "And again, she is much lower than the male."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 167779.0,
      "end_time": 169476.0,
      "text": "GG: Yeah, she sounds different."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 169500.0,
      "end_time": 175150.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing, lower pitch)"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 175174.0,
      "end_time": 176676.0,
      "text": "Yeah, she&#39;s spot-on 400."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 176700.0,
      "end_time": 178833.0,
      "text": "HS: She really is. GG: That&#39;s really bizarre."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 178858.0,
      "end_time": 182597.0,
      "text": "HS: The females are at a much lower pitch. They were around 400 hertz."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 182621.0,
      "end_time": 184914.0,
      "text": "HS: And all of the females were around that, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 184938.0,
      "end_time": 186747.0,
      "text": "They were much larger than the males,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 186771.0,
      "end_time": 190218.0,
      "text": "so they didn&#39;t have to flap their wings as fast to stay in free flight."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 190242.0,
      "end_time": 193234.0,
      "text": "GG: So they have larger wings, so they&#39;re flapping slower."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 193259.0,
      "end_time": 196583.0,
      "text": "And you noticed that all the females have the same frequency, roughly?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 196608.0,
      "end_time": 199210.0,
      "text": "And the males do, too. That&#39;s kind of interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 199450.0,
      "end_time": 200565.0,
      "text": "So that must mean something."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 200589.0,
      "end_time": 204131.0,
      "text": "Well, let&#39;s see what happens when we put the male and the female together."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 204155.0,
      "end_time": 208152.0,
      "text": "(Mosquitoes buzzing; pitch varies)"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 208176.0,
      "end_time": 210511.0,
      "text": "HS: When I put them into the same hearing range,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 210535.0,
      "end_time": 213319.0,
      "text": "I noticed that they were kind of changing their tones."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 213343.0,
      "end_time": 215605.0,
      "text": "It was kind of more dull, almost."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 215629.0,
      "end_time": 217206.0,
      "text": "(Mosquitoes buzzing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 217230.0,
      "end_time": 220969.0,
      "text": "And when I put it back in my spectrogram to see their interaction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 220993.0,
      "end_time": 223317.0,
      "text": "they were meeting at the same tone."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 223342.0,
      "end_time": 224803.0,
      "text": "GG: OK, pause."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 224827.0,
      "end_time": 227120.0,
      "text": "The males and females are singing a duet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 227144.0,
      "end_time": 230574.0,
      "text": "meaning that they adjust their wings to be able to produce a common tone."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 230598.0,
      "end_time": 233272.0,
      "text": "You have the male singing up here at G,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 233296.0,
      "end_time": 236149.0,
      "text": "and you have the female singing down here at D,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 236173.0,
      "end_time": 237461.0,
      "text": "and when they get together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 237485.0,
      "end_time": 240698.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re saying that they change the frequency of their wings"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 240722.0,
      "end_time": 242185.0,
      "text": "such that they come together?"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 242209.0,
      "end_time": 244648.0,
      "text": "HS: Yeah, exactly. GG: And they sort of sing a duet."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 244672.0,
      "end_time": 249775.0,
      "text": "(Mosquitoes gradually adjusting to identical pitch)"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 249799.0,
      "end_time": 252116.0,
      "text": "HS: They&#39;re communicating to let each other know"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 252140.0,
      "end_time": 254297.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;ve basically found a potential mate."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 254322.0,
      "end_time": 255472.0,
      "text": "GG: So in other words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 255496.0,
      "end_time": 258492.0,
      "text": "the female tends to choose a male that best sings her duet."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 258516.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260659.00000000003,
      "text": "And studies have found that if she&#39;s pregnant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 260683.0,
      "end_time": 261915.0,
      "text": "she doesn&#39;t even bother."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 262661.0,
      "end_time": 265344.0,
      "text": "So if we can understand the mosquito mating behavior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 265368.0,
      "end_time": 269445.0,
      "text": "we may be able to disrupt it in the wild and prevent diseases like malaria."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 269469.0,
      "end_time": 273349.0,
      "text": "But for now, the next time you hear a mosquito buzzing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 273373.0,
      "end_time": 276644.0,
      "text": "just pause and remember she may be in love"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 276668.0,
      "end_time": 278222.0,
      "text": "and she may be singing her song,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 278246.0,
      "end_time": 280178.0,
      "text": "looking for her perfect match."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 280202.0,
      "end_time": 281203.0,
      "text": "(Mosquito buzzing)"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 281227.0,
      "end_time": 282376.0,
      "text": "(Smack)"
    }
  ]
}